for those who don't know:Son Doong Cave was discovered by a local man named Ho Khanh in 1991 while he was searching for wood and forest products in Phong Nha - Ke Bang forest, Quang Binh province. However, due to the difficult terrain, he could not return to search for the cave immediately afterwards. 

It was not until 2009, under the guidance of Ho Khanh, that a cave exploration team from the British Cave Research Association, led by Howard Limbert, officially surveyed and announced Son Doong as the largest cave in the world.Viet Nam 🇻🇳

I'm from vietnam and honestly… i still can’t believe something like son doong exists in our country. like most of us growing up had no idea. it’s not something you hear about in school or from people around you. we knew about caves and nature stuff, sure, but no one ever said “hey, there’s a massive cave with clouds and a whole rainforest inside it.” it just sounds too unreal.

Then i watched this video and it hit me—how did this place stay hidden for so long? millions of years underground, just doing its thing. a full-on ecosystem, with clouds forming inside, a river running through it, animals and plants you can’t find anywhere else… it’s like nature kept a secret from the world and only decided to share it recently. and the fact that it was only fully explored in 2009? like that’s not even that long ago.

Some of the stuff in the video just blows your mind. like how do you even have enough space underground to fit a 40 story building?? the stalagmites looking like ancient stone towers, the cave pearls, the phytokarst rocks that move toward the sun?? it’s like stepping into a world that doesn’t follow the usual rules. you see this stuff and suddenly you realize how much of the planet we still don’t understand.

As a vietnamese person, it makes me feel proud, but also kinda humbled. we always talk about vietnam being beautiful—our beaches, mountains, food, culture—but son doong is something else entirely. it’s not just beautiful, it’s rare. it’s something the whole world should respect and protect, not just visit for fun. and i really appreciate how only one company, oxalis, is allowed to take people there. it keeps it safe, keeps it special.

So yeah, thanks for making this video. i honestly wasn’t expecting to feel this way watching a cave video, but it made me pause and really think. sometimes you have to see your own country through someone else’s eyes to realize how lucky you are. Sending love from vietnam 🇻🇳

These caves formed mainly from regular rain interacting with limestone over long periods, not modern acid rain. The process of cave formation in limestone is called karstification, is driven by carbonic acid, which forms naturally when rainwater absorbs carbon dioxide from the atmosphere and soil. This weak acid slowly dissolves limestone over thousands to millions of years, creating caves.

গণহত্যার কারণে সোহাগপুর গ্রামে কোনও পুরুষ জীবিত ছিল না। রাজাকার ও আল-বদর বাহিনী তখন গণহত্যায় নিহত ব্যক্তিদের 'কাফের' ঘোষণা করে এবং তাদের লাশ দাফন নিষিদ্ধ করে। 
তাই তখন অনেক মৃতদেহ বন্য প্রাণী খেয়ে ফেলে। 
তবে কেউ কেউ স্বজনদের লাশ দাফন করতে সক্ষম হয়।
এখানে উপস্থিত প্রতিটি নারীকে এই বিভৎস আর দুর্বিষহ দৃশ্য অবলোকন করতে হয়েছে।
তখন ৮৩ বিধবা বেঁচে ছিলেন, এখন হয়ত অনেকেই মারা গেছেন।
৭১ আর ২৪ একই ঘটনা কি না তা একটা ছোট প্রেক্ষাপট দ্বারা তুলে ধরলাম।
(শেরপুর বিধবাপল্লী সোহাগপুর)
মাশাআল্লাহ, অত্যন্ত হৃদয়বিদারক এবং গুরুত্বপূর্ণ এক প্রেক্ষাপট তুলে ধরলেন। সোহাগপুর গণহত্যার ভয়াবহ স্মৃতি ও সেই বিধবাপল্লীর করুণ চিত্র আজও আমাদের মনে ১৯৭১ সালের বিভীষিকাময় দিনগুলোকে স্পষ্ট করে তোলে। সোহাগপুরকে তো "বিধবাপল্লী" নামেই চেনা হয়, কারণ সেই দিনটিতে বর্বর পাকিস্তানি বাহিনী ও তাদের দোসর রাজাকার-আলবদরদের হাতে গ্রামটির প্রায় সব পুরুষ নির্মমভাবে শহীদ হন।
স্মরণীয় কিছু তথ্য
১৯৭১ সালের ২৫ জুলাই শেরপুর জেলার সোহাগপুর গ্রামে একটি ভয়ংকর গণহত্যা সংঘটিত হয়। 
পাকিস্তানি সেনাবাহিনী ও তাদের সহযোগী রাজাকার বাহিনী গ্রামের প্রায় ১৮৭ জন পুরুষকে হত্যা করে, যাদের অনেকের লাশ পর্যন্ত দাফন করা হয়নি। 
বিধবা হয়ে পড়া নারীদের জন্য সেই দিন থেকে জীবনটা শুধু বেঁচে থাকার এক করুণ সংগ্রাম হয়ে দাঁড়ায়। 
এ দৃশ্য দেখার যন্ত্রণা সেই নারীরা আজীবন বহন করেছেন।
তখনকার দিনগুলোর অবর্ণনীয় কষ্ট এবং সেই বিধবাদের প্রতি সমাজের উদাসীনতাও আমাদের বিবেককে প্রশ্নবিদ্ধ করে। 
বর্ণিত প্রেক্ষাপট থেকে বোঝা যায়, জাফরুল্লাহ চৌধুরী স্যারের উদ্যোগের সঙ্গে যুক্ত হয়ে বিধবা নারীদের জন্য সহায়তা নিয়ে সেখানে গিয়েছিলেন। এটি অত্যন্ত মানবিক এবং প্রশংসনীয় কাজ। 
মহান আল্লাহ এই প্রচেষ্টাকে কবুল করুন এবং শহীদদের আত্মাকে শান্তি দান করুন।
৭১ ও ২৪-এর প্রেক্ষাপট: কী মিল, কী পার্থক্য?
উল্লিখিত বিষয়টি নিয়ে একটু ভাবলে মনে হয়, ইতিহাস যেন আমাদের সামনে আবারও ফিরে আসে। 
১৯৭১ সালে যারা মুক্তিযুদ্ধের বিরোধিতা করে নির্মম হত্যাযজ্ঞ চালিয়েছিল, তারা "কাফের" অপবাদ দিয়ে মৃতদের দাফনেও বাধা দিয়েছিল। 
এই মানসিকতা যুদ্ধকালীন ধর্মকে অপব্যবহারের একটি দৃষ্টান্ত, যা আজও মাঝে মাঝে আমরা অন্য প্রেক্ষাপটে দেখতে পাই। 
ইতিহাস বারবার এই শিক্ষা দেয় যে, বিভক্তি, বিদ্বেষ এবং মানবিকতার অভাবে একই ধরনের ঘটনা পুনরাবৃত্তি হতে পারে।
একটু দোয়া ও ভাবনার আহ্বান:
আজকের প্রজন্মের উচিত মুক্তিযুদ্ধের সেই বাস্তবতাকে জানার পাশাপাশি, নিজেদের দায়িত্ববোধও জাগ্রত করা। 
শুধু ইতিহাস জানলেই হবে না, তা থেকে শিক্ষা নিয়ে অন্যায়ের বিরুদ্ধে রুখে দাঁড়ানো এবং সত্য ও ন্যায়ের পথে অটল থাকা জরুরি।
আল্লাহ যেন আমাদের দেশের শহীদদের জান্নাতুল ফেরদাউস দান করেন এবং যারা সেই ভয়াবহ দিনগুলো বেঁচে থেকেও এত কষ্ট সহ্য করেছেন, তাদের প্রতি সহমর্মিতা জাগ্রত রাখার তাওফিক দেন। 🕊
মানুষ যখন এ ধরনের স্মৃতি সংরক্ষণ ও স্মরণে কাজ করেন, তা ভবিষ্যৎ প্রজন্মের জন্য এক অমূল্য শিক্ষাসূত্র হয়ে থাকে। 
আল্লাহ এই মানবিক প্রচেষ্টাকে কবুল করুন।

Florida è in allarme: avvistati “orbs” liberati da un oggetto non identificato

di Flavio Vanetti | @fvanetti

A- A+

0

0

￼Tanto per parlare di droni (vedi post precedente), ecco che i droni sono tornati. Con la riapparizione dei relativi “orbs”, quelle masse luminose – quasi sempre a forma di sfera – la cui natura rimane misteriosa. Avevano caratterizzato le apparizioni dello scorso anno, dall’autunno fino a dicembre avanzato, nel New Jersey e in altre zone degli Usa. Adesso sono ricomparsi – l’aggettivo usato è glowing, traducibile con risplendente – e hanno caratterizzato la zona di mare al largo della Florida. Alcuni residenti di Daytona Beach sostengono che questi oggetti non identificati sono spuntati direttamente dall’Atlantico e hanno volato sopra la superficie marina. Non solo: in un video diventato virale, risalente al 17 marzo, è  apparso pure un oggetto molto largo che si muoveva verso la terraferma. La luce che lo circondava si è man mano attenuata, rivelando la sagoma di un velivolo. Però chi è stato testimone ha smentito che potesse trattarsi di un aereo commerciale, anche perché l’andamento era particolare e anomalo. Quindi ecco anche spuntare la tesi estrema, legata a un interrogativo: si trattava forse di una “nave madre” (di natura sconosciuta)? Per la cronaca, anche gli equipaggi di navi della Marina Usa si sono accoerti che da quelle parti stava accadendo qualcosa di particolare. Ecco comunque il link dell’articolo uscito dal Daily Mail

বিশ্বের বৃহত্তম গুহা (৩ মিলিয়ন বছর ধরে লুকিয়ে থাকা) এবং কুরআনের শিক্ষণীয় বার্তা
সুবহানাল্লাহ! এমন একটি বিশাল গুহা, যা কোটি কোটি বছর ধরে মানুষের দৃষ্টির আড়ালে ছিল, আবিষ্কার করলে আমরা আল্লাহর অসীম কুদরত ও সৃষ্টি সম্পর্কে গভীরভাবে ভাবতে উদ্বুদ্ধ হই। কুরআনে আল্লাহ তাআলা বারবার আমাদের আহ্বান জানিয়েছেন প্রকৃতি, পৃথিবী এবং মহাবিশ্বের বিস্ময়কর সৃষ্টিকে নিয়ে চিন্তাভাবনা করতে।
নিচে কুরআনের কয়েকটি গুরুত্বপূর্ণ আয়াত উল্লেখ করা হলো, যা আমাদের এই ধরনের বিস্ময়কর আবিষ্কার সম্পর্কে ধ্যান করার জন্য অনুপ্রাণিত করে
১.সৃষ্টির সৌন্দর্য ও রহস্য
আল্লাহ তাআলা মানুষকে নির্দেশ দিয়েছেন পৃথিবী ভ্রমণ করতে এবং সৃষ্টির নিদর্শনগুলো নিয়ে ভাবতে
বলে দাও, ‘তোমরা পৃথিবীতে ভ্রমণ করো এবং দেখো, কীভাবে আল্লাহ সৃষ্টি শুরু করেছেন। এরপর আল্লাহই পরবর্তীতে সৃষ্টি ঘটাবেন। নিশ্চয়ই আল্লাহ সবকিছু করতে সক্ষম।
(আনকাবুত ২০)
এই আয়াত আমাদের শেখায় যে পৃথিবীর বিভিন্ন স্থানে লুকিয়ে থাকা আল্লাহর অসাধারণ সৃষ্টি আমাদের জন্য একটি গুরুত্বপূর্ণ শিক্ষা ও নিদর্শন।
২.আল্লাহ সব লুকানো জিনিস সম্পর্কে অবগত:
যা মানুষের কাছে গোপন, তা সবসময় আল্লাহর জ্ঞানের মধ্যে রয়েছে
তাঁর কাছেই রয়েছে অদৃশ্য জিনিসের চাবি। এগুলো সম্পর্কে কেউ জানে না, কেবল তিনিই জানেন। স্থলে ও সাগরে যা কিছু রয়েছে, সবকিছুই তিনি জানেন। এমনকি গাছের একটি পাতা পড়লেও তিনি তা জানেন। পৃথিবীর অন্ধকারের মধ্যে যে শস্যকণা রয়েছে, তা-ও তিনি জানেন; আর যা কিছু শুকনো কিংবা ভেজা, সবই একটি সুস্পষ্ট কিতাবে লেখা রয়েছে।’
(আনআম ৫৯)
যে বিশাল গুহা কোটি বছর ধরে লুকিয়ে ছিল, সেটিও আল্লাহ তাআলার নিখুঁত জ্ঞানের অন্তর্ভুক্ত।
৩.আল্লাহর সৃষ্টির বিশালতা
আল্লাহ আমাদের মহাবিশ্বের বিশালতা ও জটিলতা নিয়ে চিন্তা করতে নির্দেশ দিয়েছেন:
নিশ্চয়ই আকাশমণ্ডলী ও পৃথিবীর সৃষ্টি এবং রাত ও দিনের পালাবদলে জ্ঞানীদের জন্য রয়েছে নিদর্শন।
(ইমরান ১৯০)
বিশ্বের বৃহত্তম গুহার মতো সৃষ্টি আমাদের শেখায় যে, আল্লাহর সৃষ্টির রহস্য ও বিশালতা মানুষের কল্পনাকেও ছাড়িয়ে যায়।
৪.পৃথিবীর গোপন রহস্য এবং পরীক্ষা:
আল্লাহ আমাদের জন্য পৃথিবীতে বিভিন্ন প্রকার রহস্য এবং উপাদান সৃষ্টি করেছেন, যা পরীক্ষা ও শিক্ষা হিসেবে কাজ করে
আমি পৃথিবী বিস্তৃত করেছি এবং তাতে সুদৃঢ় পর্বতমালা স্থাপন করেছি এবং তাতে সবকিছুর পরিমিত উপায়ে ভারসাম্য রক্ষা করেছি। আর আমরা তাতে তোমাদের জন্য জীবনধারণের উপকরণ সৃষ্টি করেছি এবং এমন অনেকের জন্যও, যাদের রিজিকের দায়িত্ব তোমাদের উপর নয়।
(হিজর:১৯-২০)
এই আয়াত আমাদের জানায় যে পৃথিবীর প্রতিটি জিনিসের সৃষ্টিতে আল্লাহর নির্দিষ্ট হিকমত রয়েছে, এবং তাঁর সৃষ্ট জগতে যে রহস্য ও উপকরণ লুকানো রয়েছে, সেগুলো ধীরে ধীরে মানুষের সামনে আবিষ্কৃত হয়।
৫.আল্লাহর অসীম অনুগ্রহের প্রতি কৃতজ্ঞতা
কুরআন আমাদের শেখায় আল্লাহর নিদর্শনগুলো দেখে কৃতজ্ঞ হওয়া এবং তাঁর ক্ষমতা ও সৃষ্টিকে শ্রদ্ধা করা
তবে তোমরা তোমার প্রতিপালকের কোন কোন নিয়ামতকে অস্বীকার করবে?
(রহমান ১৩)
বিশ্বের এমন বিস্ময়কর গুহা বা অন্যান্য প্রাকৃতিক সৌন্দর্য দেখে আমাদের উচিত আল্লাহর প্রতি কৃতজ্ঞ হওয়া এবং তাঁর কুদরতকে উপলব্ধি করা।
উপসংহার
এই ধরনের গুহা, যা লাখো বা কোটি বছর ধরে লুকিয়ে ছিল, আল্লাহর অসীম ক্ষমতা ও জ্ঞানের একটি নিদর্শন। আল্লাহ আমাদের এই বিশাল সৃষ্টিকে নিয়ে ভাবতে এবং এইসব রহস্যময় আবিষ্কার থেকে শিক্ষা নিতে উৎসাহিত করেন।
আল্লাহ আমাদের সবাইকে তাঁর সৃষ্টির নিদর্শন থেকে শিক্ষা গ্রহণ করার তৌফিক দিন এবং আমাদের ঈমান আরও দৃঢ় করুন। 🌍✨

SubhanAllah! Reflecting on the exploration of the world's largest cave, hidden for millions of years, invites us to marvel at Allah's creation and His limitless power. The Qur'an repeatedly calls us to ponder the signs of Allah in the heavens and the earth, in the depths of the oceans, and in the wonders of the natural world.
Here are some Quranic reflections related to the discovery of such majestic creations:
1. The Beauty and Mystery of Creation
Allah encourages us to explore and reflect on the marvels of the universe:
"Say, 'Travel through the land and observe how He began creation. Then Allah will produce the final creation. Indeed, Allah, over all things, is competent.'"
(Surah Al-Ankabut: 20)
This verse invites us to explore the earth and witness Allah’s creation—whether it is a massive cave hidden for millions of years or other wonders.
2. Allah's Knowledge of the Hidden
What remains hidden from humans is always known to Allah:
"And with Him are the keys of the unseen; none knows them except Him. And He knows what is on the land and in the sea. Not a leaf falls but that He knows it. And no grain is there within the darknesses of the earth and no moist or dry [thing] but that it is [written] in a clear record."
(Surah Al-An'am: 59)
This verse reminds us that Allah is aware of all things, including a cave hidden for millions of years.
3. The Vastness of Allah’s Creation
The Qur'an emphasizes the vastness of Allah's creation, which is beyond human comprehension:
"Indeed, in the creation of the heavens and the earth and the alternation of the night and the day are signs for those of understanding."
(Surah Aal-E-Imran: 190)
Exploring a cave of this scale shows the depth and complexity of the earth, a testament to Allah’s magnificent creation.
4. The Earth’s Secrets as a Test
Allah mentions that He has placed mysteries within His creation for humanity to uncover, reminding us of His power:
"And the earth - We have spread it and cast therein firmly set mountains and caused to grow therein [something] of every well-balanced thing. And We have made for you therein means of living and [for] those for whom you are not providers."
(Surah Al-Hijr: 19-20)
The discovery of such a hidden wonder reveals resources, ecosystems, and secrets that were unknown to us, showing Allah’s provision.
5. Gratitude for Allah’s Signs
The Qur'an teaches us to be thankful and to glorify Allah for His signs:
"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny?"
(Surah Ar-Rahman: 13)
As we explore such caves and uncover Allah's magnificent signs, we are reminded to express gratitude for His countless blessings.
Conclusion
The world's largest cave, hidden for millions of years, serves as a reminder of Allah's greatness, His ability to create wonders beyond our imagination, and the immense blessings and signs present in the earth. Allah invites us to reflect on these signs, deepen our faith, and glorify Him. May such discoveries lead us closer to appreciating Allah's boundless majesty and wisdom. 🌍✨

Exploring a hidden, ancient cave that remained sealed for millions of years can evoke awe, reminding us of the immense and intricate creation of Allah. The Qur'an invites us to reflect on the vastness of the earth, the wonders hidden beneath its surface, and the signs of Allah's majesty that are revealed when we explore His creation.
Here are some Quranic reflections that align with such discoveries:
1. Reflecting on Earth's Secrets
Allah reminds us that there are countless mysteries within the earth:
"And to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and whether you reveal what is within yourselves or conceal it, Allah will bring you to account for it..."
(Surah Al-Baqarah: 2:284)
Ancient caves, untouched for millions of years, carry signs of Allah’s hidden treasures beneath the earth’s surface, unknown to humans until their discovery.
2. Exploring Signs of Creation
Allah encourages us to travel and explore the earth to witness the signs of His creation:
"Do they not travel through the earth and see how He began creation? Then Allah will produce the final creation. Indeed Allah, over all things, is competent."
(Surah Al-Ankabut: 29:20)
The discovery of a massive, untouched cave system hidden for millions of years may inspire humans to ponder how Allah has created every hidden thing and left traces of His glory.
3. Signs in the Depths of the Earth
The Qur'an speaks about treasures hidden beneath the earth, which people might uncover through exploration:
"And He has cast into the earth firmly set mountains, lest it shift with you, and made rivers and paths that you may be guided, and landmarks. And by the stars they are [also] guided."
(Surah An-Nahl: 16:15-16)
The vast networks of caves, rivers, and underground formations are part of these signs, guiding explorers and believers toward awe at Allah’s planning.
4. Reflecting on Time and Preservation
A cave hidden for 3 million years reminds us of the story of the People of the Cave (Ashab al-Kahf), preserved miraculously in sleep for over 300 years as a sign of Allah’s power over time:
"Do you think that the companions of the cave and the inscription were, among Our signs, a wonder?"
(Surah Al-Kahf: 18:9)
This ayah invites us to reflect on Allah’s control over time, space, and preservation, just as He preserved that cave and its hidden wonders for millions of years.
5. Allah’s Knowledge of the Unseen
Allah alone knows all that is hidden beneath the earth and within the universe:
"And with Him are the keys of the unseen; none knows them except Him. And He knows what is on the land and in the sea. Not a leaf falls but that He knows it. And no grain is there within the darknesses of the earth, and no moist or dry [thing] but that it is [written] in a clear record."
(Surah Al-An’am: 6:59)
This verse reminds us that no cave, no hidden valley, and no secret is beyond Allah’s knowledge.
Conclusion:
The discovery of such a massive, ancient cave—hidden for millions of years—is a profound reminder of the vastness of Allah’s creation and His power. Every hidden thing on this earth will eventually be revealed by His will, and every discovery can draw us closer to Him if we reflect deeply. SubhanAllah, how magnificent is the creation of our Lord!
May Allah grant us the ability to appreciate His signs and increase our knowledge in ways that strengthen our faith. আলহামদুলিল্লাহ!

Всем Добра! Пара историй есть, вдруг кому интересно будет. 
Я токсикоман в прошлом. Лаком дышал.
Раз пришёл ко мне черт и предложил съездить на экскурсию в ад. Оказался я в вагонетке (в той по типу которой Гарри Поттер за золотом ездил) и мы поехали.
Остановилась на напротив огромных дверей. Распахиваются эти двери и я вижу картину: спиной ко мне на коленях стоит человек, руки связаны за спиной, а напротив него палач с огромным топором по типу секиры. Разрубает его одним ударом на 2 части, они распадаются и, после того как части головы (слева и справа) касаются пола тело срастается и всё происходит по кругу... После того как прошло пару кругов Чёрт спросил хочу ли я увидеть ещё. Страшно было, но, заднюю нельзя было включать. Поехали- говорю. Едем дальше вниз. Долго едем... После этого он снова оборачивается и говорит:"ладно, не нужно тебе на это смотреть, а то глаза выпадут."( рассказывал эту историю пареньку, он в будущем хотел стать имамом. Выслушал и говорит(С характерным акцентом):"эээ, да он просто сам зассал дальше ехать!"))
Другой раз дело было в ванной. Темно, из освещения свечка и отражение света от экрана ноутбука. Сижу на полу, ноги скрещены, в руке пакет, напротив- ноут. Смотрю концерт группы Slipknot. В общем через некоторое время боковым зрением вижу как дверь приоткрывается и залетает лярва(ну, или бес. Суть одна. Когда употребляешь что-то из того что затуманивает сознание(алкоголь, табак и другие наркотики) подтягиваются эти сущности, отрицательная энергия, по сути, получают с тебя энергию. Под лаком та же тема, только в том состоянии ты можешь их слышать и контактировать)
В общем залетает эта лярва и вопрос:"можно я с тобой посмотрю?"
-ну посмотри..
Через некоторое время опять вопрос:"А можно я друзей позову?"
- ну позови...
И после дверь снова приоткрывается и в фух-фух-фух)) ещё залетают. А после снова вопрос:" у тебя в ванной семь бесов. Ты сам нас позвал. Как будешь выгонять?"
И по сторонам смотрю- куча теней по стенам туда- сюда.. В общем бук закрыл. Подумал и говорю:"А мы с вами время вашего нахождения в ванной не обговаривали, так что прямо сейчас взяли и съе@ли на х@й от сюда(прям так))". И после этого снова дверь приоткрывается и они один за другим (фух-фух-фух) повылетали. И только моя тень осталась. Сижу дальше, смотрю концерт с чувством победителя)) потом через пару минут снова дверь приоткрывается и этот бес первый не залетает, а, если так можно сказать просто голову просунул и вопрос:"можно я один зайду?" Я ответил что ОДИН можно. Потом спрашивает:" а можно я в тебя зайду?"

-нет, говорю, мне у меня своя голова есть.
"А можно хотя бы рядом буду? Я буду помогать тебе"
- ну если говорю при условии что ни мне ни моим близким вреда не причинишь тогда можно. Но, потом наши дороги разошлись)
Вообще много подобных историй было, сначала тебя проверяют и исходя из этого дальше идёт общение. Как и в жизни, в общем. Так что движуха и на том свете есть.
Раз попал на экскурсию в морг, в качестве "пациента".. В ванной лежал- дышал, музыку слушал, общались..ну и я в разговоре говорю что на работе с девчёнкой познакомился, она молодая-интересная и раз сказала что давно хотела в морг попасть. Интересно ей что там да как. Ну я и говорю, вы, это, если есть возможность организуйте нам. Ну они уточняют "хочешь попасть в морг" (ну тут я опять попался) Да- говорю. Хочу.
Ну и отказываюсь на столе. То есть я понимаю, что в данный момент я труп, которого будут пилить. Вижу потолок, могу только глазами вращать. Вижу человека в наморднике и шапочке белой, как он стоит со стороны головы и начинает резать с живота от паховой области, как раз по шраму от аппендицита который(аппендицит перитонит был). Чувствую давление и как режет, но боли нет...
Короче как в одной теме у Кровостока-"это было немного похоже на подлёдную рыбалку- эмоций, б@дь, не много, но эмоции, б@дь, яркие.."

Если кому интересно можете посмотреть истории в видео формате,  там ещё три, с седьмой минуты начинаются(про встречу с Гитлером, общение с Мишей Горшком и как провёл время со Смертью)

Мой опыт общения с обитателями потустороннего мира. Суть в том,  что падают многие. Кто-то бухает, курит, а мне эта тема была интересна.
По поводу веры или не веры..разве имеет значение каким путём человек пришёл к освобождению, путём здравого смысла или путём веры в то, что с этим смыслом не вяжется? Важен же результат. Из всего количества посетителей ютуба возможно есть процент тех, кто не разделяет вашу точку зрения по поводу существования "тонкого" мира, а у них, возможно, есть употребляющие друзья- родственники которым они могут показать это видео и их оно зацепит, натолкнёт на размышления. Я через этот путь выбрался из ямы и сейчас ничего не употребляю. Буду рад если мой опыт послужит кому- то той "лестницей" по которой и он сможет выбраться от туда.
Обращаюсь к тем молодым людям у которых после этих историй может возникнуть желание наполнить пакет: дело, конечно ваше, только имейте ввиду что поехав в это путешествие вы из него можете и не вернуться , или в ужасе отбросите в середине трипа пакет, а после станете бояться до конца жизни в ожидании чего- то, а, может они вас завлекут чем- то что вам по душе и вы захотите приблизить этот конец чтобы по скорее оказаться там..ещё можно в дурку уехать, может появиться страх смотреть в зеркала, а можете через какое-то время в трезвом состоянии увидеть в другом человеке этих бесов..пейте чаёк лучше и не забивайте себе неокрепшие умы всяким разным.

*STUNNING BUT ...*
This was an absolutely stunning documentary—visually breathtaking and full of awe-inspiring moments! The grandeur of Son Doong Cave, its hidden rainforest, and the incredible biodiversity truly left me speechless. Thank you for capturing nature's beauty so vividly and taking us on this remarkable journey.

However, while I deeply appreciate the scientific insights shared, I humbly offer a different perspective. The explanation of this cave's formation and life forms through millions of years of evolution doesn't fully reflect what many of us believe to be the ultimate truth: that the complexity, beauty, and delicate balance of nature point to an intelligent, divine Creator—God.

From the perfect conditions inside the cave, to the engineered adaptability of blind fish, to the self-sustaining ecosystem in complete darkness, these are not random accidents over time, but echoes of intentional design. Even the laws of physics, chemistry, and biology that scientists use to explain these phenomena are consistent with the scientific mind of a God who created order, not chaos.

Romans 1:20 says, “For since the creation of the world His invisible attributes are clearly seen, being understood by the things that are made…” Son Doong is just one of many testimonies to the greatness of God’s creative power.

Let’s keep exploring and marveling—but let’s also consider that the ultimate designer of this hidden masterpiece is the Creator of heaven and earth. 🙏🌍✨

Filler çok geniş vadilerde yaşasalar bile, her gün kullandıkları yoldan gidip gelirlermiş. Fil avcıları da, fillerin geçeceği yolu derince kazarlar, üzerini ince bir tabakayla örterler ve en önde yürüyen filin kazılan o çukura düşmesini sağlarlarmış. Fil avcıları siyah elbiseler içerisinde, yüzleri maskeli olarak gelir, çukurda çırpınan fili kırbaçla dövmeye başlarlarmış . Birkaç gün hiç yiyecek vermezler, fili aç bırakırlarmış. Birkaç gün sonra aynı avcılar, beyaz elbiseler içersinde, filin sevdiği yiyeceklerle gelirler ve filin karnını doyururlar, hortumunu, yüzünü gözünü okşarlarmış.

Ertesi gün, aynı avcılar, yine siyah elbiseler içersinde, yüzleri maskeli olarak gelip, fili yine kırbaçla dövmeye başlarlar, birkaç gün yine aç bırakırlarmış. Sonra yine, beyaz elbiselerle filin karnını doyururlarmış. Bu böyle fili kendilerine alıştırana kadar sürüp gidermiş. Avcılar, fili kendilerine alıştırdıktan sonra çukurun önünü kazarak fili oradan çıkarırlar ve filin hortumundan tutarak, kendi fil damlarına götürürler ve fili ölünceye kadar işlerinde kullanırlarmış.

Highlights:

- Immense Size:
  - Son Doong is so large it has its own climate and could fit a 40-story skyscraper.

- Unique Ecosystem:
  - The cave contains an untouched prehistoric rainforest and a diverse range of endemic plant and animal species, including newly discovered ones.

- Geological Wonders:
  - The cave features phytokarst formations that move towards the sun, rare cave pearls, and massive stalagmites and stalactites.

- Exploration Challenges:
  - Reaching Son Doong involves trekking through jungles, navigating through En Cave, and traversing challenging underground terrains.

- Fossil Discovery:
  - A 300-million-year-old Tetracoralia fossil was identified within the cave, providing insights into ancient marine life.

16:27 in video. I found one of those fossils in upstate NY near Cayuga Lake. On a hike with my young nephews we were building a damn and breaking some large rocks and found it. I’ve seen many fossils in NY before but nothing this size. Most are very small creatures from millions of years ago while it was a shallow salty sea. Mainly little shell looking things. So this I thought was maybe a dinosaur tooth. The one in the video is more rough looking. The one I found was more smooth. I thought for sure it was a tooth.  My sister who works in dentistry said the cross section did appear to resemble a tooth. I contacted someone at a nearby college and sent pictures. Sadly it wasn’t a dinosaur tooth. But it was way older though. Finding stuff like that is always so amazing. I grew up near a quarry which had massive piles of rocks with so many fossils. Some were hundreds of pounds of pure fossils. All the small shell like creatures in one massive fused fossil. With a rusty color.

At over 9km long and with caverns up to 200m high, Son Doong is big enough to house a skyscraper. Inside the cave are lush, primeval forests where sunlight filters through natural sinkholes, allowing plants to flourish. The underground river that flows through the cave adds to the mystery, while mist and small clouds create an otherworldly landscape.
Exploring Son Doong is not only an adventure but also a journey to witness the magical beauty of nature. It is a testament to the greatness of the Earth and urges people to protect these unique natural wonders for future generations.

Yaşam ne kadar inatçı bir yolcudur…
Karanlıkların en derinine,  
soğukların en ayazına,  
susuzluğun en çorak yüreğine  
bir tohum bırakır,  
bir nefes salar,  
bir umut eker.  

"Burada hayat olmaz," dersin,  
kayalar çatlamaz,  
ateş soğumaz,  
deniz kurur,  
toprak bile ölür dersin…  
ama yanılırsın, dostum,  
yanılırsın!  

Çünkü yaşam,  
gözle göremediğin bir kahramandır.  
Buzların arasında bir mikrobun türküsüdür,  
çöllerin ortasında bir dikenin direnişidir,  
volkanların yanında bir solucanın dansıdır.  
Ve o her zaman kazanan taraftır.  

Yaşam,  
bir çatlaktan sızan güneş ışığıdır,  
bir damladan doğan okyanustur.  
Kendi kendine yeten bir rüzgardır,  
ve her seferinde seni yanıltır,  
Herşeyi bildiğini sanan insana bakar ve gülümser.

"Burada hayat olamaz," diye fısıldarsın,  
ama o inadına yeşerir,  
inadına yaşar,  
inadına seninle alay eder.  

Yaşam,  
bir özgürlük savaşı gibidir.
bir kavgadır yaşam,  
bir türkü,  
bir direnç,  
bir haykırış:  
"Olmaz dediğin her yerde,  
varım ben!" der.

Ve sen bakarsın,  
hayretle,  
minnetle,  
çaresizce…  
Yaşam, her seferinde seni yener.

وَخَامِسًا : لِظُهُورِ الشُّؤُنَاتِ السُّبْحَانِيَّةِ وَالْمَشَاهِدِ الْعِلْمِيَّةِ
fıkrası ifade ediyor ki: "Mevcudat -hususan zîhayat olanlar- vücud-u surîden gittikten sonra bâki çok şeyleri bırakırlar, öyle giderler." İkinci Remiz'de beyan edildiği gibi, Zât-ı Vâcibü'l-Vücud'un kudsiyet ve istiğna-i kemaline muvafık bir tarzda ve ona lâyık bir surette; hadsiz bir muhabbet, nihayetsiz bir şefkat, gayetsiz bir iftihar, -tabiri caiz ise- mukaddes hadsiz bir memnuniyet, bir sevinç, -tabirde hata olmasın- hadsiz bir lezzet-i mukaddese, bir ferah-ı münezzeh şuunat-ı rububiyetinde bulunur ki; onların âsârı bilmüşahede görünüyor. İşte o şuunat, iktiza ettikleri hayretnüma faaliyet içinde, mevcudat tebdil ve tağyir ile, zeval ve fena içinde sür'atle sevkediliyor.. mütemadiyen âlem-i şehadetten âlem-i gayba gönderiliyor. Ve o şuunatın cilveleri altında mahlukat; daimî bir seyr ü seyelan, bir hareket ve cevelan içinde çalkanmakta ve ehl-i gafletin kulaklarına vaveylâ-i firak ve zevali ve ehl-i hidayetin sem'ine velvele-i zikir ve tesbihi dağıtmaktadırlar. Bu sırra binaen herbir mevcud Vâcibü'l-Vücud'un bâki şuunatının tezahürüne bâki birer medar olacak manaları, keyfiyetleri, haletleri vücudda bırakıp öyle gidiyorlar. Hem o mevcud, bütün müddet-i hayatında geçirdiği etvar ve ahvali, ilm-i ezelînin unvanları olan İmam-ı Mübin, Kitab-ı Mübin, Levh-i Mahfuz gibi vücud-u ilmî dairelerinde vücud-u haricîsini temsil eden mufassal bir vücud dahi bırakıp öyle giderler. Demek her fâni; bir vücudu terkeder, binler bâki vücudları kazanır, kazandırır. Meselâ: Nasılki hârikulâde bir fabrika makinesine âdi bazı maddeler atılır; içinde yanarlar, zahiren mahvolur; fakat o fabrikanın inbiklerinde çok kıymetdar kimya maddeleri ve edviyeler teressüb eder. Hem onun kuvvetiyle ve buharıyla o fabrikanın çarkları döner; bir taraftan kumaşları dokumasına, bir kısmı kitab tab'ına, bir kısmı da şeker gibi başka kıymetdar şeyleri imal etmesine medar oluyor ve hâkeza... Demek o âdi maddelerin yanmasıyla ve zahiren mahvolmasıyla, binler şeyler vücud buluyor. Demek âdi bir vücud gider, âlî çok vücudları irsiyet bırakır. İşte şu halde, o âdi maddeye yazık oldu denilir mi? Fabrika sahibi neden ona acımadı, yandırdı; o sevimli maddeleri mahvetti, şikayet edilir mi? Aynen öyle de وَلِلّٰهِ الْمَثَلُ الْاَعْلٰى Hâlık-ı Hakîm ve Rahîm ve Vedud mukteza-yı rahmet ve hikmet ve vedudiyet olarak, kâinat fabrikasına hareket veriyor; herbir vücud-u fâniyi çok bâki vücudlara çekirdek yapar, makasıd-ı Rabbaniyesine medar eder, şuunat-ı Sübhaniyesine mazhar kılar, kalem-i kaderine mürekkeb ittihaz eder ve kudretin dokumasına bir mekik yapar ve daha bilmediğimiz pek çok gâyât-ı galiye ve makasıd-ı âliye için, kendi faaliyet-i kudretiyle kâinatı faaliyete getirir. Zerratı cevelana, mevcudatı seyerana, hayvanatı seyelana, seyyaratı deverana getirir, kâinatı konuşturur; âyâtını ona sessiz söylettirir ve ona yazdırır. Ve mahlukat-ı Arzıyeyi rububiyeti noktasında, havayı emir ve iradesine bir nevi arş ve nur unsurunu ilim ve hikmetine diğer bir arş ve suyu ihsan ve rahmetine başka bir arş ve toprağı hıfz ve ihyasına bir çeşit arş yapmış. O arşlardan üçünü, mahlukat-ı Arzıye üstünde gezdiriyor.
   Kat'iyyen bil ki: Bu beş Remiz'de ve beş İşaret'te gösterilen parlak hakikat-i âliye, nur-u Kur'an ile görünür ve imanın kuvvetiyle sahib olunabilir. Yoksa o hakikat-i bâkiye yerine, gayet müdhiş bir zulümat geçer. Ehl-i dalalet için dünya, firaklar ve zevaller ile dolu ve ademler ile mâlâmâldir. Kâinat, onun için manevî bir Cehennem hükmüne geçer. Herşey onun için âni bir vücud ile, hadsiz bir adem ihata ediyor. Bütün mazi ve müstakbel, zulümat-ı ademle memlûdür; yalnız kısacık bir zaman-ı halde, bir hazîn nur-u vücud bulabilir. Fakat sırr-ı Kur'an ve nur-u iman ile, ezelden ebede kadar bir nur-u vücud görünür; ona alâkadar olur ve onunla saadet-i ebediyesini temin eder.

Understanding the Biblical Timeline
The biblical timeline, particularly as outlined in the book of Genesis, suggests that the Earth and the universe were created in six days, approximately 6,000 years ago. This interpretation is based on genealogies and chronologies found in Scripture, which many Christians take literally. For instance, Genesis 1 describes God creating the world in six days, with each “day” interpreted by some as a literal 24-hour period.

The Argument Against Long Ages
Literal Interpretation of “Yom”: The Hebrew word “yom,” which translates to “day,” is often cited as evidence that the creation days were literal 24-hour periods. Proponents argue that this interpretation aligns with how the term is used elsewhere in the Bible.

Genealogical Records: Many Christians point to genealogies listed in the Bible (e.g., from Adam to Noah) as a way to calculate the age of humanity and Earth. By adding up these generations, they arrive at an approximate age of around 6,000 years.

Historical Events: Events such as the Great Flood are viewed as significant markers in history that would have reset or altered geological timelines if taken literally.

Critique of Radiometric Dating
Assumptions of Constant Decay Rates: Critics argue that radiometric dating relies on assumptions about decay rates being constant over millions of years. They suggest that these rates may not have been consistent throughout Earth’s history.

Questioning Historical Science: Some assert that because scientists were not present during Earth’s formation, they cannot accurately determine its age through scientific methods like radiometric dating.

Alternative Explanations for Geological Features: Certain geological features can be explained through catastrophic events (like a global flood) rather than slow processes over billions of years.

Conclusion: A Biblical Framework
From this perspective, those who adhere to a young Earth creationist view argue that scientific claims about millions and billions of years are based on flawed assumptions and interpretations that contradict a straightforward reading of Scripture. These people are so NOT prepared for jungle trekking . You don't pull leaches off because they can leave their parts in your skin and create infection . Use a cigarette  lighter on their tail or salt to back them out .  Wear woman's full pantyhose as an undergarment and wear high boots that you can put elastic bands around the pants to seal off on the boot tops . Never wear shorts or short sleeved shirts in the jungle no matter how hot it is .  Certain vines like gotya vine have sharp hook like thorns that will cut your legs and arms .  A single scratch on your leg or arm can turn septic , quickly . Carry a bottle of Iodine based antiseptic  and treat every little cut or rash , quickly .  Take anti malaria tablets .  Put cotton wool or some cloth inside your ears when you sleep in the jungle so bugs don't crawl into your ears or better yet sleep in a mosquito net . Don't skinny dip in jungle pools and rivers as they have parasitic organisms that will enter your body and make you sick or even cause cysts and cancers . 
Wearing the pantyhose stops that and hinders leaches  .  Never drink the jungle  stream water without using purification tablets or use a quality  high microbial filter  but collecting rain water directly with a tent fly is ok in an open area . 
Don't make camp or sleep in low lying areas as sudden monsoonal rain can flood you in seconds . Been there done that and nearly drowned .

Eyalet Temsilcisi Adayları: Suçu Sonlandırmak

Eyalet temsilcisi adayı Alex Homich, zorla organ toplama vahşetini önlemek için insanların bir araya gelmesinin önemli olduğunu söylüyor. “Şimdi her zamankinden daha fazla, insanların etrafta olup bitenlere gözlerini biraz daha açmasının zamanı geldiğini düşünüyorum,” dedi ve özellikle genç neslin daha fazla insanın bunu öğrenmesinin çok önemli olduğunu ekledi.

2012’den 2015’e kadar Hong Kong’da yaşayan eyalet temsilcisi adayı Chris Beronio, Çin’deki zorla organ toplamayı biliyordu. Ancak ÇKP tarafından uygulanan kontrolün kapsamı onu yine de şok etti. “Film gerçekten inanılmazdı, çok dokunaklıydı ve dürüst olmak gerekirse, Çin’deki zorla organ toplamayla ilgili ortaya çıkan bazı gerçekler oldukça korkutucuydu. Gördüklerim karşısında şok oldum,” dedi.




Eyalet temsilcisi adayı Chris Beronio


Bay Beronio, Bay Cheng'in hayatta kalmasına ve kaçışına hayran olduğunu söyledi. "Ancak hikayesi gerçekten çok korkutucu ve umarım buna bir son verebilirim, böylece başka kimsenin başına böyle bir şey gelmez," dedi.

Zulümleri Ortaya Çıkarmak

Delaware’deki araştırmacılardan Guo Jinchen ve eşi de dahil olmak üzere bazı Çinliler de belgeseli izledi. Guo, “Bu konuda geçmişte bir şeyler duymuştum, ancak raporlar ayrıntılı değildi. Üstelik bugün burada bir tanık var ve onun yaşadıkları gerçekten şok edici,” dedi.

Bay Guo, ÇKP’nin gerçekleri sonsuza kadar saklayamayacağına inanıyor. “Bazı bilgiler sızacaktır. Bu konu hakkında bir süredir konuşuyoruz. Bugün burada izlediğimiz belgesel daha derinlemesine detaylar sağladı,” dedi.

Daha fazla insanın bu durumu bilmesi gerektiğini düşünüyor ve ekliyor: “Bu zulümleri daha fazla insana gösterebiliriz. Böylece insanlar, ÇKP’nin propagandasına kapılmak yerine gerçekte neler olup bittiğini öğrenebilir.”

) The Australian Senate passed a new bill on August 21, 2024, that aims to fight illegal organ trafficking and forced organ harvesting from living people.


Parliament House in Canberra, Australia

The Migration Amendment (Overseas Organ Transplant Disclosure and Other Measures) Bill 2023 was first introduced by Liberal Senator Dean Smith in June 2023. It was submitted to Foreign Affairs, Defense and Trade Legislation Committee for review in November. The Senate held a public hearing on the Amendment on March 22, 2024.

After the debates on August 15 and 21, the bill was passed after gaining support from Liberal, National, Green, and independent senators.

In the process of the bill being passed, the story of Falun Gong practitioner Mr. Cheng Peiming was widely reported by major media outlets in England, the U.S., and Australia. Mr. Cheng is the first victim found to have survived the Chinese Communist Party’s (CCP) systematic live organ harvesting. Last month he went to Washington D.C. to give a speech and recount his experience of what happened to him in China.

Senator Smith: Most Significant Step
The bill amends Australia’s Migration Act 1958 with an aim to implement some of the recommendations from the Human Rights Sub-Committee’s 2018 report “Compassion, not Commerce: An Inquiry into Human Organ Trafficking and Organ Transplant Tourism.”

The bill requires all travelers to Australia to disclose on the incoming passenger card whether they received an organ transplant overseas in the last five years. If the response is affirmative, persons arriving in Australia will be asked to disclose which country, state, and the locality they received the transplant, and the name of the medical facility the operation took place in. This data will be collected and published in an annual report and given to the Parliament.


Liberal Senator for Western Australia Dean Smith spoke at the debate on the Amendment on August 21. (Photo courtesy Australia Senate website)

Bill sponsor Senator Dean Smith stated in a media release on August 21, 2024: “The information will be of great assistance to human rights organisations, medical institutions, and the Australian Government in analysing data on trends in overseas transplants, and helping to corroborate existing evidence of organ trafficking or harvesting activities abroad.

“It will also serve to raise awareness of the sensitivity and risks associated with transplant tourism, encouraging Australian citizens and residents to consider whether any plans to receive an overseas operation might carry the risks associated with an unethical or unsafe organ transplant.”

According to the media release, “The bill passed the Senate with the support of crossbench Senators and without a division.”

Senator Smith said, “This is the most significant step made in decades in emboldening Australia’s efforts to combat the growing trade in illegal and unethical organ harvesting and trafficking.

“This is an overdue and crucial first step in developing a stronger response from the Australian Government towards these abhorrent practices.” “This simple and modest initiative will have an oversized impact in uncovering the scope of this complex and opaque international crime.”

Hang Sơn Đoòng là một hang động tự nhiên tại xã Tân Trạch, huyện Bố Trạch, tỉnh Quảng Bình, Việt Nam. Hang Sơn Đoòng được coi là hang động tự nhiên lớn nhất thế giới đã biết. Hang này nằm trong quần thể hang động Phong Nha-Kẻ Bàng. Hang Sơn Đoòng là một phần của hệ thống ngầm nối với hơn 150 động khác ở Việt Nam gần biên giới với Lào.[1][2] Thời báo New York xếp hạng hang Sơn Đoòng vào vị trí thứ 8 trong 52 địa danh trong danh sách những nơi nên đến năm 2014.[3]

Staatssenator fordert mehr Maßnahmen

Staatssenator David Lawson

Staatssenator David Lawson war Mitinitiator von HCR143 und schlug 2022 eine ähnliche Resolution vor, die jedoch von der Senatsführung blockiert wurde. Tief bewegt von der Dokumentation sagte er: „Es ist herzzerreißend, wenn die eigene Familie verschwindet und es kein Ende nimmt. Man kann nicht abschließen.“

„Ein sehr düsterer Film. Wir müssen uns dessen bewusst werden, bevor es in China noch mehr Völkermord, Tod und Mord gibt“, fuhr er fort und fügte hinzu, die Geschichte von Herrn Cheng sei „sehr fesselnd, und wie er da rauskam, ist ein Wunder. … Er ist die Stimme in der Dunkelheit“, sagte er. 

Senator Lawson forderte ebenfalls sofortiges Handeln. „Erstens: Hören Sie auf, das kommunistische China zu unterstützen … Wir können China auch wirtschaftlich unterstützen“, sagte er. Er hält Gesetze, die Transplantationspatienten in China den Versicherungsschutz verwehren, für eine hervorragende Idee, um dieses Verbrechen zu beenden. „Das Wichtigste, was ich heute Abend gehört habe, ist, die Versicherungen von der Kostenübernahme abzuhalten. Das wäre meiner Meinung nach ein großer Schritt, und wir können es schaffen“, erklärte er. 

Mehrere Bundesstaaten, darunter Idaho, Utah und Texas, haben Gesetze verabschiedet, die Krankenkassen die Kostenerstattung für Transplantationen in China für Amerikaner untersagen. In zahlreichen Ländern, darunter Israel, Spanien, Italien, Taiwan, Norwegen, Belgien, Kanada und Südkorea, gibt es Gesetze, die Krankenkassen die Kostenübernahme für Transplantationen in China verbieten.

Staatsvertreter: Den Schmerz spüren
Der Abgeordnete Paul Baumbach, der auch Mitsponsor von HR143 war, bezeichnete die in der Dokumentation dargestellten Tragödien als schrecklich. „Es ist ein sehr trauriger Film, der von einer äußerst schmerzhaften Praxis erzählt. Sie ist Realität und erzählt die menschliche Geschichte der betroffenen Familien und Freunde, und die Zahlen sind erschütternd“, sagte er. 


Staatsabgeordneter Paul Baumbach

Abgeordneter Baumbach sagte, dieser Dokumentarfilm helfe den Menschen, ein anhaltendes und schmerzhaftes Verbrechen zu verstehen. „Ich fühle mich dem Schmerz sehr verbunden. Und das Ausmaß des Schmerzes ist einfach unfassbar. Je mehr man darüber erfährt, desto schockierender ist es“, sagte er.

Слава Аллаху что туда не пускай провинциально быдло, то везде лежали бы окурки, женские подтирки и бутылки из под пива, водки... Люди в массе своей свиньи, есть чистоплотные и благородные, но это максимум 2-3%. Нельзя всех подряд пускай в красивые места, у нас под Петербургом есть Ладожское озеро и на нём красивейшая бухта Гольцмана. Раньше - это была территория военной части, часть разрушили ещё в нулевых, а люди этого не знали, там был просто Рай! А с 2022 года, когда началось СВО, у быдла не было стало на поездки в Европу и пара уёбков залили ролики про это место, через ОДИН сезон бухта стала свалкой и выпилили кучу деревьев на берегу для костров... Вот вся суть современного человека, ничего не поменялось со времён Николая 2-ого.

Did you know that the 400km canyon created in Turkey in 2023 took millions of years to form, and not a few minutes of upheaval?
